---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="The Hot Dog"
  description="A hot dog is more than a quirky logo. It's a symbol of nostalgia, connection, creativity, and continuity. The origin story of the codewizwit mark."
>
  <article class="hot-dog">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="hot-dog-hero section-cream section" aria-labelledby="hd-heading">
      <div class="container hot-dog-hero-inner">
        <img
          src="/images/codewizwit-logo.jpg"
          alt="codewizwit logo: a block print style hot dog illustration, rendered with visible grain texture"
          class="hot-dog-logo"
          width="400"
          height="276"
          loading="eager"
        />
        <div>
          <p class="label label-gold">The Symbol</p>
          <h1 id="hd-heading" class="hot-dog-title">The Hot Dog</h1>
          <p class="hot-dog-lede">
            A symbol of human connection that's followed me my entire life.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Story -->
    <section class="section-cream section-sm" aria-labelledby="hd-story">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 id="hd-story" class="sr-only">The story</h2>
        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            Some of my earliest memories are of sharing Chicago dogs with my
            dad at Gene &amp; Jude's. No ketchup allowed. Small moments that
            taught me how the simplest things can hold the most meaning.
          </p>
          <p>
            Years later, that same symbol showed up again when I hand-carved a
            hot dog block print for my college capstone project at DePaul. A
            physical artifact made with ink, pressure, and patience.
          </p>
          <p>
            The version you see now is an AI-simplified rendering of a photo
            of that original print. A bridge between memory and technology,
            past and future.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Meta-Proof -->
    <section class="section-dark section" aria-labelledby="hd-proof">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 id="hd-proof" class="hot-dog-section-heading" style="color: var(--color-cream);">
          The meta-proof
        </h2>
        <div class="prose" style="color: var(--color-gray-light);">
          <p>
            Think about it. The simplest human connection (a father and
            daughter sharing a hot dog) became a hand-carved print, which
            became a photograph, which became an AI-rendered logo. The meaning
            didn't get lost. It got amplified.
          </p>
          <p>
            This is a reminder that while AI can refine creativity and
            carry a symbol forward, the spark, the story, the deeply human part
            always comes first.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Closing -->
    <section class="section-cream section" aria-labelledby="hd-close">
      <div class="container text-center">
        <h2 id="hd-close" class="hot-dog-closing">
          More AI. More human.
        </h2>
        <p class="hot-dog-closing-sub">
          That hot dog is more than a quirky logo. It's a reminder of where I
          come from, what I care about, and the future I want to help build.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .hot-dog-hero-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .hot-dog-logo {
    width: clamp(200px, 30vw, 360px);
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  }

  .hot-dog-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .hot-dog-lede {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 28rem;
  }

  .hot-dog-section-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .hot-dog-closing {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .hot-dog-closing-sub {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: var(--max-width-prose);
    margin-inline: auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hot-dog-hero-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .hot-dog-logo {
      margin-inline: auto;
    }

    .hot-dog-lede {
      margin-inline: auto;
    }
  }
</style>
